Wheelin' Around University Park
A Journey on Wheels
Jessica McPhaul

Draft

As an eager explorer and nature enthusiast, there's nothing quite like the feeling of the wind in my face, the steady rhythm of my wheels on the pavement, and the thrill of discovering new places right outside my door. On any given day, you can find me riding my bike or scooting through the streets of SMU, Highland Park, and University Park—each trip a new adventure, a fresh perspective on the life and energy pulsing through these vibrant neighborhoods.

Whether it's the laughter of families enjoying a sunny afternoon at the park, the quiet charm of historic architecture, or the radiant hues of a sunrise spilling over the rooftops, every ride offers a unique snapshot of this community. I’m constantly captivated by the balance of urban life and natural beauty, from the bustling campus scenes to the quiet paths lined with towering oaks and blooming gardens. It’s here, in these little details, that I find the true spirit of the area.

Join me on this journey as I wheel through the heart of University Park, capturing the essence of bicycles, dogs, families, food, sports, and those unforgettable moments when the sun paints the sky in a blaze of colors. Let’s explore together, as I share my favorite routes, hidden gems, and the simple joys of life on two wheels.
